Package.Name: README
Package.InternalNotes:
Naming scheme:
TankSkinsRemodels_{Nation}_{Class}_{TankDisplayName}_{ModName}_{Author}_{Remodel/Reskin}

{TankDisplayName} = The name you see in the garage, NOT the internal name.
{ModName} = The authors name for the mod, excluding any tank names (Viper, Stormtrooper, ect)
{Author} = Original Author. Not the maintainer. That may be used in the author field.
{Remodel/Reskin} = Remodel is when the model is changed. Reskin is when the skin of the tank is changed
Remodels tend to have XML files, but not always.
Reskins are almost always DDS files. Never have XML files

Mods are to have public dev urls from mod hosting sites, or sites akin to Github. Anything else will be removed. The mod hosting sites may not have illegal mods on them (IE: pkmods). WGMODS is preferred.

All mods in this category are to be in wotmod files. They also must have load_order.xml patches.
All mods must include at least 1 image of the mod. Its better to have 4-5, from both the garage and battle.

Tags are not required in this category, as the packageName takes care of what that would be used for. But tag them if you want.

Conflicting packages are not required due to the load_order.xml patching. Should you find a mod that conflicts with another, even after using this patch, please notify me (The Illusion). 

If you have any questions, please ask.
Package.Author: The Illusion
